The paper deals with feature selection for multi-view data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a new method for unsupervised feature selection that is specifically designed for multi-view data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions that the proposed method is evaluated on four real-world datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions that the proposed method is formulated as a constrained optimization problem and solved using a Quasi-Newton based method, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) or Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, and cs.CL.
